TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {9955=Freshman Year (2009-10): Skated in all 31 games as a freshman … netted five goals and added four assists for nine points … scored her first two collegiate goals and added an assist in Princeton's win at Vermont … scored in a tie with Rensselaer … added two assists in a win over Union … had an assist in a win at Yale … scored in Princeton's win at Brown … added a power-play goal in a loss at Syracuse. textBeforeTable: Personal: Full name is Kelly Elizabeth Cooke ... daughter of George and Jennifer Cooke ... father attended Western New England College and is a bank analyst ... mother attended Dartmouth and is a teacher ... has an older brother Evan that graduated from Boston College and was a member of the sailing team ... birthday is Oct. 29 ... major is English. Before Princeton: Attended Noble and Greenough School and played for Assabet Valley as well ... scored 23 goals and added 22 assists for 45 points in 29 games as a senior captain at Nobles ... led team to NEPSAC Division 1 Championship and was the NEPSAC tournament's Most Valuable Player ... scored the game-winning goals in the NEPSAC semifinal and championship games and had nine points in the tournament ... was an All-ISL honoree and the team won the ISL Championship ... also captained the Assabet Valley team to several in-season tournament championships and the U19 national quarterfinals ... was an All-ISL selection and team won ISL and were NEPSAC runner-ups as a Nobles junior ... also played four years of varsity lacrosse and two years each of varsity soccer and field hockey at Nobles, earning All-ISL honors in both field hockey and lacrosse and winning ISL titles in all three ... attended several USA Hockey National Development camps and won two USA Hockey National Championships with Assabet Valley at the U12 and U16 levels. Freshman Year (2009-10): Skated in all 31 games
